    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2022-03-30</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2023-06-23T18:39:07Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>This bill reestablishes an initiative related to China within the National Security Division of the Department of Justice (DOJ) and outlines the goals and requirements for this initiative.</p> <p>In 2022, DOJ ended a program named the China Initiative. This bill reestablishes and renames it the CCP Initiative to (1) counter nation-state threats to the United States; (2) curb spying by the Chinese Communist Party (CCP) on U.S. intellectual property and academic institutions; (3) identify and prosecute individuals engaged in trade secret theft, hacking, and economic espionage; and (4) protect U.S. critical infrastructure from foreign threats.</p> <p>DOJ must annually brief specified congressional committees on the progress and challenges of the initiative.</p> <p>The initiative terminates six years after enactment of this bill.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
